svg.text: MOOCs-Points
After Identifying the subjects and experts, time table will be prepared and put in the
University Website and circulated to all the Colleges( through proper channel).
The
External/ Subject Experts
need not come to the University for delivering the content.
o
They can deliver the class from anywhere, if they have laptop/ desktop (with
Webcam and Mike) and internet with good bandwidth.
o
MOOCs team will provide them necessary links and softwares regularly to deliver the
course content.
o
For every MOOCs expert user name and password will be created.
Required technical support will be given by the Coordinator and his team.
Initially online training will be given for the external expert and demo classes
will be conducted ( before the actual course starts)
o
Each subject expert should take
1 hour 50 minutes class
. There will be two classes
per week.
o
Material like course notes, e-books, PPTs etc. should be provided by the expert
Uploading PPTs and Material will be done by MOOCs team
o
According the timetable day to day support will be given by the coordinator and his
team.
Foreign Subject experts may be given priority in fixing slots in the MOOCs
time table.
According to the MOOCs timetable the class timetable for each branch
should be prepared.
MOOCs timetable is for all the constituent and affiliated colleges, it may not
be changed.
o
MOOCs team will coordinate the running of all MOOCs as per the timetable
Syllabus coverage will be monitored
Extra slots will be provided in the time table, if any subject expert needs any
extra classes to cover the syllabus
If expert cannot take class on a particular day, due to some reasons, the same
class may be rescheduled to another vacant slot in the timetable and
intimation will be given to all the colleges.
But experts need to intimate the same at least one day before, in order
to send the information to all the colleges.
o
MOOCs team will interact with all the subject experts and different colleges
regularly.
o
There will be online technical support for all the colleges throughout the semester
from then MOOCS team.
o
Every fort night online feedback from all the participant colleges will be taken
o
Course material and videos will be distributed to all the participant colleges regularly.
There is no financial commitment from the MOOCs opted colleges.
Notice will be sent to all constituent & affiliated colleges to give willingness for MOOCs, to
identify college SPOC and Internal mentor for each subject.
o
List of Colleges enrolled will be collected
o
List of Students enrolled for each subject from each college will be collected and
maintained.
Selecting Internal mentor is very important
o
The Internal faculty should attend all the classes along with the students and will help
them in solving the assignments and clarify the doubts.
o
This is considered as full semester training
for the internal faculty.
o
The Internal faculty is the interface between the online mentor and student.
